The paper proposes a decoding algorithm for staircase codes, which are commonly used in high-speed optical transport networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NET) sub-categories. Additionally, the algorithm is designed to reduce the effect of undetected component code miscorrections, which involves manipulating and analyzing data. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
